Generate an independent (explanatory) variable $\bm{x}$ and {\bf two} samples of a dependent variable $\bm{y}$ assuming that
$$y_i = 4 - 2x_i + \epsilon_i \ , \quad \epsilon_i\sim \N(0,0.5^2) \ .$$



\begin{center}
<<eval=T,fig.width=3.5,fig.height=3.3>>=
